race.comment: Looks a handy race with several progressive types lining up. STEEL TSUNAMI (1) is definitely one of those, with two wins from six starts. He's got to lug the 60.5kg but he has good gate speed, can roll forward and might just be better than these. ARTICULATING (5) mixes his form but the ability is there. He's another one that can settle handy and be hard to beat with the claim. SETTEVELI (7) was very good first-up, then only plain last start. Perhaps they ride him cold to hit the line like he did first-start. He's got the turn of foot to get past most of these. DUCHESS OF SUSSEX (9) can run well first-up, while SUMADARTSON (8) might be ready to peak third-up.
